comments:
All the alien words started with smi or smu, so I focused mostly on the other "half" of them when trying to memorize them. On top of that I tried to associate them with other words I was familiar with that would be close to the alien words and I could somewhat associate with the objects (smipygs I connected with pigs (in a blanket) due to its cylindric shape, smuvyds with virus because of the spiky texture, smikobs with a knob because it somewhat looked like one to me, smutons with croutons because it was lumpy, smipads I associated with stimpacks because it looked like a medical device (inaler or injector) to me. Smikens was one I separated the two things, associating the word itself with kittens, and then associating the object with a nerf gun loader, and then I just connected the two things. Smuteg was very losely associated with "smooth eggs" but it was more of a case of remembering it as the one missing). And I also kept saying the words out loud to help memorize them.
The hardest parts for me were the first 2 or 3 times with the cards, when I still hand't fully associated words to objects, then one point between the middle and the end of the first phase when I had repeated the words so much that they were starting to sound weird to me and I had to refocus because I was tripping over the letters and had a bit of a harder time remembering the proper word, and then the second phase was also hard because it wasn't always easy to keep up with the speed of the flashing words and I failed to read some properly only catching certain letters, which were enough most of the time but made me feel unsure of my answer.
